Author 侯蔚琳。
Author Hou Wei Lin.
大城小事cityandlife。
Little things of the big city.
关注城市中的人和生活方式。
Focus on people and lifestyles in cities.
如阳光下的下午茶，岁月静好，心中喜悦。
If the afternoon tea in the sun, the years quiet, happy heart.
。
.
经常是下午两点，护士长出去告诉挂号者，医生还没吃午饭。
It was often two o'clock in the afternoon when the matron went out to tell the registered man that the doctor had not had lunch.
满满一房间的患者竟立刻安静下来，急忙为我让了一条“路”出来。
A room full of patients immediately quiet down, hastily for me to make way for a "road."
文 |侯蔚琳春节前，我们发热门诊突然转来一位新冠肺炎疑似者。
Before Hou Wei-lin's Spring Festival, our fever clinic suddenly turned in a suspected New Crown Pneumonia.
我套上防护服，进入层流病房采集患者生命特征一手数据，并安抚其焦虑情绪。
I put on protective clothing, entered the laminar ward to collect the patient's vital characteristics first-hand data, and soothed his anxiety.
接下来的几天，就医人数持续攀升。
The number of people seeking medical treatment continued to climb over the next few days.
一天下来，光喊号喉咙就哑了。
At the end of the day, the voice just shouted hoarse.
经常是下午两点，护士长出去告诉挂号者，医生还没吃午饭。
It was often two o'clock in the afternoon when the matron went out to tell the registered man that the doctor had not had lunch.
满满一房间的患者竟立刻安静下来，急忙为我让了一条“路”出来。
A room full of patients immediately quiet down, hastily for me to make way for a "road."
我觉得这是医患之间互相体谅的心灵之“桥”。
I think it is a bridge of understanding between doctors and patients.
短短几步路，却是由最为可贵的人心铺成的。
Just a few steps away, but by the most valuable people's minds paved.
当时场面非常感人，眼泪在眼眶里打转。
The scene was so moving that tears began to well up in her eyes.
我低下头，迅速“过桥”去扒几口饭，又回来为患者看病。
I bowed my head, quickly "across the bridge" to pick a few rice, and back to the patient.
某晚下班到家，喉咙嘶哑疼痛，声音完全发不出来了。
One night I came home from work, my throat was hoarse and sore and my voice was completely lost.
父亲说赶快量个体温看看。
Father said to take a temperature at once.
当看到38.1摄氏度时，心里咯噔一下。
When you see 38.1 degrees Celsius, click in your heart.
母亲立刻给全家戴上口罩。
The mother immediately put a mask on the family.
我被隔离到了家里的单间。
I was quarantined into a private room at home.
次日一早，朝着女儿远远挥手道别，让孩子爸爸把她带去奶奶家。
The next morning, waving goodbye to her at a distance, the father took her to Grandma's.
只是没想到，从出生到现在没怎么离开过身边的女儿，这一别竟是一个月。
I just didn't think that from birth to the present little left his daughter, this is a month.
很长一段时间里，与女儿视频都是她和我都憋着泪，挂断之后才敢哭。
For a long time, with her daughter video is she and I are suffocating tears, hang up before crying.
好在体温第二天复原。
Fortunately, the temperature recovered the next day.
说实话，咳得睡不着觉、腹泻出现时是会有心理压力的。
To tell the truth, coughing can not sleep, diarrhea occurs when there will be psychological pressure.
唯家人、同事的支持是我最大的动力。
Only the support of my family and colleagues is my biggest motivation.
查了胸部CT没有肺炎，很快便恢复健康，再次投入工作。
Chest CT was examined without pneumonia, and soon recovered and returned to work.
只是母亲在去年12月肾病发作，大大小小手术、拔管子需经历五六场。
Only the mother in December of a kidney attack, large and small surgery, tubing to go through five or six.
没想到第一场手术刚过，疫情便开始了。
I didn't expect the outbreak to start just after the first operation.
我在前线奋斗时，母亲肚子里、背后留置的管子都时时煎熬着她。
As I struggled on the front lines, the tubes that my mother kept in her stomach and behind her back kept tormenting her.
感谢泌尿科的仲医生，精心手术，耐心答疑，让我解除了后顾之忧。
Thanks to the urology department doctor, meticulous surgery, patient answers, let me ease the worry.
晚上下班回到家里，我为手术期间不能动弹的母亲擦身，洗头，换药，熬药……上海启动一级响应之后，我们发热门诊成为“战疫”最前线。
Back home from work at night, I can not move during the operation for the mother to scrub, shampoo, change medicine... Shanghai launched a first-class response, our fever clinic became the "epidemic" front-line.
院领导非常重视，全院的兄弟科室都来人支援我们，给发热门诊减轻了一些压力，也让我们能更迅速鉴别疑似新冠患者。
The hospital leadership attaches great importance to the hospital's brother departments have come to support us, the fever clinic to relieve some of the pressure, but we can more quickly identify suspected new crown patients.
隔离病房建立后，我们的疑似会诊隔离流程更加完善。
After the establishment of isolation ward, our suspected consultation isolation process is more perfect.
医院里出了一批又一批医护人员驰援武汉，支援公卫中心。
Hospital out of a batch of medical personnel rushed to Wuhan to support the public health center.
每一次离别都壮怀激烈，每一句保重都揪心不已。
Every departure is hugely intense, and every sentence is filled with anxiety.
然而，我仍能看到胜利曙光。
Still, I can see the light of victory.
坚持，坚持，让我们再坚持一段时日！征集令阳春三月，万物复苏。
Hold on, hold on, let's stick to it for a while! Call for a March, and everything will come back.
在抗击疫情的战斗中，我们迎来了春天，《新民周刊》也迎来了新闻线索和故事征集的第二弹。
In the fight against the epidemic, we ushered in the spring, "New People's Weekly" also ushered in the news clues and the second round of story collection.
如今，经历了一个多月休眠的城市正在逐渐苏醒，各行各业都开始有序复工复产。
Now, after more than a month of dormancy of the city is gradually waking up, all walks of life began to orderly resumption of work.
不论您是企业老板、管理者，还是普通员工；又或者，您是老师、家长，还是学生本人……我们希望了解复工复产复学过程中的困难，或暖心故事。
Whether you're a business owner, a manager, or an employee, or whether you're a teacher, parent, or student... we'd like to know about the difficulties of getting back to work, or a warm heart story.
如果你是抗疫一线的医生护士，疫情期间拍下了珍贵的摄影作品，也欢迎联系我们投稿。
If you are a first-line doctor and nurse against the epidemic, you have taken valuable photographs during the epidemic and are welcome to contact us for contributions.
当然，抗击新冠肺炎疫情的相关故事，我们仍然欢迎。
Of course, the story of fighting the outbreak of New Crown Pneumonia is still welcome.
希望广大读者朋友，提供相关线索，说出你的故事，让我们用新闻留存这一切。
I hope that the general reader friends, provide relevant clues, tell your story, let us use the news to retain all this.
